Literature Review: Mars seismology has emerged as a crucial field of study in planetary science, providing insights into the internal structure and seismicity of Mars. The InSight mission, launched in 2018, has revolutionized our understanding of Mars' interior with its high-quality seismometers and robotic installation on the ground. This literature review aims to summarize the key findings from the InSight mission and its implications for Mars seismology.
